28/05/2004
STRASBOURG, France -- An agreement establishing the Network of Local Authorities of Southeast Europe was signed by representatives of 14 associations of local governments in Southeastern Europe (SEE), during the plenary session of the Council of Europe (CoE) Congress on Thursday (27 May). The CoE Congress launched the initiative following three years of informal co-operation within the framework of the Stability Pact for SEE. The network aims to improve services provided by local authorities. (CoE press release - 27/05/04)
